1.	Install VirtualBox 
    Select window hosts https://www.virtualbox.org/wiki/Downloads

2.	Install Vagrant
    Select window 64bit https://www.vagrantup.com/downloads.html

3.  Go to any directory, and run vagrant command
    vagrant init

4.  Replace Vagrantfile content with the following lines

    # -*- mode: ruby -*-
    # vi: set ft=ruby :
    
    Vagrant.configure("2") do |config|
    
       #server
       config.vm.define "server" do |server|
        server.vm.box = "ubuntu/bionic64"
        server.vm.hostname = "server"
        server.vm.network "private_network", ip: "192.168.30.14"
        server.vm.provider "virtualbox" do |vb|
         vb.name = 'server'	
         vb.customize ["modifyvm", :id, "--memory", 2048]
        end
        server.vm.provision "shell", inline: <<-SHELL
         sudo -s
         apt-get install unzip
         wget https://releases.hashicorp.com/consul/1.4.1/consul_1.4.1_linux_amd64.zip
         unzip consul_1.4.1_linux_amd64.zip
         mv consul /usr/local/bin
         mkdir /etc/consul.d
        SHELL
       end
    
       #agent
       config.vm.define "agent" do |agent|
        agent.vm.box = "ubuntu/bionic64"
        agent.vm.hostname = "agent"
        agent.vm.network "forwarded_port", guest: 8500, host: 8500
        agent.vm.network "private_network", ip: "192.168.30.15"
        agent.vm.provider "virtualbox" do |vb|
         vb.name = 'agent'	
         vb.customize ["modifyvm", :id, "--memory", 2048]
        end
        agent.vm.provision "shell", inline: <<-SHELL
                  sudo -s  sudo
                  apt-get install unzip
                  wget https://releases.hashicorp.com/consul/1.4.1/consul_1.4.1_linux_amd64.zip
                  unzip consul_1.4.1_linux_amd64.zip
                  mv consul /usr/local/bin
                  mkdir /etc/consul.d
        SHELL
       end
    end

5.  Run vagrant
    vagrant up

6.  Configure server with the following commands
    vagrant ssh server
    sudo -s
    consul agent -server -bootstrap-expect=1 -data-dir=/tmp/consul -node=server -bind=192.168.30.14 -enable-script-checks=true \
    -config-dir=/etc/consul.d -ui -client=0.0.0.0

7.  Go to agent server, run the following commands
    vagrant ssh agent
    sudo -s
    consul agent -data-dir=/tmp/consul -node=client -bind=192.168.30.15 -enable-script-checks=true -config-dir=/etc/consul.d \
    -join 192.168.30.14 -client=0.0.0.0
